Durban - KwaMashu police seized three firearms from three different men in three different incidents in KwaMashu A, E and K sections, north of Durban. Captain Nqobile Gwala, police spokesperson, said police arrested three men between the ages of 33 and 34 and seized three firearms with 13 rounds of ammunition. “A 33-year-old suspect was arrested in K-section with a revolver and a round of ammunition in his possession. Police proceeded to KwaMashu hostel, A section where they found another 33-year-old suspect with a 9mm pistol with five rounds of ammunition at Isivumelwano Road. When police were on their way to the police station in E-section, Malandela Road they searched a 34-year-old male who was also found with a pistol and seven rounds of ammunition in his possession. He was immediately arrested,” explained Gwala. She said the men were charged with the possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. Major General Bheki Langa, KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner, said: “These firearms will be subjected for ballistic testing to ascertain if they were used in our pending cases or other serious and violent crimes in the country.” KwaZulu-Natal police have seized more than 200 firearms since the start of 2018. Daily News